The paper discusses the use of Quantifier Elimination (QE) technology for automated reasoning in economics, which is a topic related to logic and automated reasoning. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science). The paper also mentions the application of QE in economics education and research, which could fall under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.CE (Computational Economics). Additionally, the paper discusses a bank of QE examples gathered from economics literature, which could be related to cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
